<div id="review_919876395" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/919876395" />
    <a title="Emily " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2377230-emily"><img alt="Emily " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486778976p2/2377230.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/919876395?book_show_action=true">Apr 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emily " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emily " href="/user/show/2377230-emily">Emily </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2377230-emily?shelf=a-own-it">a-own-it</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2377230-emily?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer919876395" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer884855454603604638">What a crock of shit. I loved the first book and gave it 5 stars. This one... man, I hate it. It&apos;s nothing even like the first book. It&apos;s just a bunch of political/religious/philosophical non-sense. The Pilgrims from the first book are basically secondary characters here. They aren&apos;t really even the focus of the story anymore. I spent almost the entire book just wishing the Shrike would slaughter everyone so this book would be over.<br/><br/>Too much poetry<br/>Too much boring descriptions of people traveling </span>
  <span id="freeText884855454603604638" style="display:none">What a crock of shit. I loved the first book and gave it 5 stars. This one... man, I hate it. It's nothing even like the first book. It's just a bunch of political/religious/philosophical non-sense. The Pilgrims from the first book are basically secondary characters here. They aren't really even the focus of the story anymore. I spent almost the entire book just wishing the Shrike would slaughter everyone so this book would be over.<br /><br />Too much poetry<br />Too much boring descriptions of people traveling - walking really far, endless descriptions of farcaster travels, really boring descriptions of traveling in the datacore etc.<br />Too much tedious political backstory details<br />BORING TEDIOUS BORING<br /></span>
